%md # Functional Connectivity Analysis
We anlyze functional connectivity based on spiking activity of 23 neuron. In this analysis we consider our work based on two spiking data:

* **Raw** spiking data
* **VLMC** (Variable Length Markov Chain) fitted spiking data

For each spiking data we consider 18 different scenarios based on epochs, conditions and in/out status:

* In the receptive field **in**
    1. Visual epoch without stimulation **Vis-In-NoStim**
    2. Memory epoch without stimulation **Mem-In-NoStim**
    3. Saccade epoch without stimulation **Sac-In-NoStim**
    4. Visual epoch with stimulation **Vis-In-Stim**
    5. Memory epoch with stimulation **Mem-In-Stim**
    6. Saccade epoch without stimulation **Sac-In-Stim**
    7. Visual epoch difference **Vis-In-Diff**
    8. Memory epoch difference **Mem-In-Diff**
    9. Saccade epoch difference **Mem-In-Diff**
* Outside the receptive field **out**
    1. Visual epoch without stimulation **Vis-Out-NoStim**
    2. Memory epoch without stimulation **Mem-Out-NoStim**
    3. Saccade epoch without stimulation **Sac-Out-NoStim**
    4. Visual epoch with stimulation **Vis-Out-Stim**
    5. Memory epoch with stimulation **Mem-Out-Stim**
    6. Saccade epoch without stimulation **Sac-Out-Stim**
    7. Visual epoch difference **Vis-Out-Diff**
    8. Memory epoch difference **Mem-Out-Diff**
    9. Saccade epoch difference **Mem-Out-Diff**

For each scenario we evaluated functional connectivity based on four method:

* Cross-Correlation
* Mutual Information
* A graphical method based on **Hawkes Multivariate Point Process** 
* Normalized compression similarity **NCS**

def histDfCreator(resDf :org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame , bucket :Int, method :String, epoch :String, io :String) :org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = {
    
    val (startValues,degree) = rawResDf.filter($"method" === method && $"epoch" === epoch && $"in/out" === io).select($"degrees").map(v => v.getDouble(0)).rdd.histogram(bucket)
    val zippedValues = startValues.map(_.toInt).zip(degree)
    val rowRDD = zippedValues.map( value => HistRow(value._1,value._2))
    val histDf = spark.createDataFrame(rowRDD)
    return histDf
}

val spikingDataList = Array("Raw", "VLMC")


val frVisualAndMem = spark.read
                    .format("csv")
                    .option("inferSchema", "true")
                    .option("header", "true")
                    .load("/data/Firing Rate/VisAndMemFrAll.csv")
                    
val frSaccade = spark.read
                    .format("csv")
                    .option("inferSchema", "true")
                    .option("header", "true")
                    .load("/data/Firing Rate/SaccadeFrAll.csv")
                    
                    
val rawResDf = spark.read
                    .format("csv")
                    .option("inferSchema", "true")
                    .option("header", "true")
                    .load("/data/Raw/NetworkInformations/all_chain_network_info.csv")
                    .groupBy($"neuron", $"method", $"epoch", $"in/out")
                    .agg(avg($"closeness_centrality").alias("closeness_centrality"), avg($"eigenvector_centrality").alias("eigenvector_centrality"), avg($"betweenness_centrality").alias("betweenness_centrality"), avg($"harmonic_centrality").alias("harmonic_centrality"), 
                    avg($"load_centrality").alias("load_centrality"), avg($"degrees").alias("degrees"), avg($"average_shortest_path").alias("average_shortest_path"), avg($"average_clustering").alias("average_clustering"), avg($"omega").alias("omega")
                    , avg($"sigma").alias("sigma"), avg($"density").alias("density"))
                    

val vlmvResDf = spark.read
                    .format("csv")
                    .option("inferSchema", "true")
                    .option("header", "true")
                    .load("/data/VLMC/NetworkInformations/all_chain_network_info.csv")
                    .groupBy($"neuron", $"method", $"epoch", $"in/out")
                    .agg(avg($"closeness_centrality").alias("closeness_centrality"), avg($"eigenvector_centrality").alias("eigenvector_centrality"), avg($"betweenness_centrality").alias("betweenness_centrality"), avg($"harmonic_centrality").alias("harmonic_centrality"), 
                    avg($"load_centrality").alias("load_centrality"), avg($"degrees").alias("degrees"), avg($"average_shortest_path").alias("average_shortest_path"), avg($"average_clustering").alias("average_clustering"), avg($"omega").alias("omega")
                    , avg($"sigma").alias("sigma"), avg($"density").alias("density"))
                    
val allResDf = rawResDf.withColumn("SpikingData", lit(spikingDataList.apply(0)))
                    .union(vlmvResDf.withColumn("SpikingData", lit(spikingDataList.apply(1))))

val methodList = rawResDf.select($"method").dropDuplicates.collect.map(_.apply(0).toString)
val epochList = rawResDf.select($"epoch").dropDuplicates.collect.map(_.apply(0).toString)
val inOutList = rawResDf.select($"in/out").dropDuplicates.collect.map(_.apply(0).toString)


val histDfRaw = epochList.map({x => 

    methodList.map({y => 
    
        inOutList.map({z => 
        
            histDfCreator(rawResDf, 15, y, x, z)
                .withColumn("in/out", lit(z))
                .withColumn("method", lit(y))
                .withColumn("epoch", lit(x))
                
        }).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
        
    }).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
    
}).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
  .withColumn("SpikingData", lit(spikingDataList.apply(0)))


val histDfVlmc = epochList.map({x => 

    methodList.map({y => 
    
        inOutList.map({z => 
        
            histDfCreator(vlmvResDf, 15, y, x, z)
                .withColumn("in/out", lit(z))
                .withColumn("method", lit(y))
                .withColumn("epoch", lit(x))
                
        }).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
        
    }).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
    
}).reduce((df1, df2) => df1.union(df2))
  .withColumn("SpikingData", lit(spikingDataList.apply(1)))
  
  
val histDf = histDfRaw.union(histDfVlmc)

allResDf.registerTempTable("Result")
histDf.registerTempTable("HIST")
frVisualAndMem.registerTempTable("FR_VM")
frSaccade.registerTempTable("FR_SAC")
